For all the way until Yugoslav unification, which in our universe didn't occur until 1928, yes. How will I do it? Don't know.

by Wejas » Sun Jan 09, 2022 10:54 am

The Empire of the Great Qing wrote:A cliché in regards to the armed forces of a small, fictional country in a contemporary setting: millions, even tens of millions, of soldiers serving in a military of a small country. A small country. Usually a military of a small country like the ones seen in Europe has something between tens of thousands to hundreds of thousands. I don’t know what you all are thinking but I’m going to act like what you’re all exactly thinking: “but dude, didn’t a few European countries have armies of a million soldiers before?”. Yeah, but I’m talking about armies of small countries in a contemporary setting, not the 1900s.

There's another thing - in modern war, bigger =/= better.

If your nation is a small, MT, and western country - HOI4-esc tactics such as "throw more conscripts at the pillbox" are kinda counter-intuitive when said nation likely has guided artillery, bomber aircraft, and drones - or is allied with nations that do. Especially in an era of intense media scrutinization where a single soldier dying in battle can spark headlines. But unless your nation has a near-infinite budget, you can't have both a large and high-quality military. If Sweden, for example, were to conscript 2 million soldiers and give them all US-tier equipment (because non-combat roles don't exist on NS), they would be spending 35 billion on infantry alone - or about 5.6 times its military budget in 2020. There'd definitely be no room left in the budget for Gripens.
